															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1888434&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610182935" alt="djkaktus" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1888434)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/djkaktus" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1888434); return false;" >djkaktus</a></span> <span class="odate time_1418536645 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">14 Dec 2014 05:57</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2179252">
									

<p>This is a rewrite of the old SCP-715, &quot;Clone Booth&quot;, by yellowdrakex. Images of the original article and the comment section thereof are included in the files of this page.</p>
<p>There were a ton of people who looked at this in chat, so I won't try to name you all. Thanks to anybody who got a chance to, I had a real blast with this one!</p>
<p>As always, your comments, critiques and criticisms are all very much welcome and appreciated!</p>
<p>Edit: IMAGE CREDITS!</p>
<p>The first image is from wikimedia commons user Visitor7, and is licensed under CC 3.0.</p>
<p>Second image is from <a href="http://beccalovesart.blogspot.com/2011/03/vintage-photobooth.html">here</a>, and I'm currently attempting to get a hold of the original uploader. Based on the description of the image, they're likely public domain by now.</p>
<p>Last image is public domain.</p>
<p>Additional images and such were all produced by me!</p>

