<p>Egh&#8230;</p>
<p>On the other, this is really well-done and creepy, especially the pictures, and the final note. It's a good update to a skip that, quite frankly, made me want to punch someone whenever I read it because of the rather&#8230; unfortunate implications it made.</p>
<p>On the one hand, the Author Avatars are <em>really</em> jarring, and that fact that Dr. Bright is the director of Site 19 <em>terrifies</em> me, especially if that damn list is canon. I seriously got the chills just thinking about that.</p>
<p>But, I'm afraid the SSAA stuff just detracts from it too much for me. I don't mind Rights so much (though I am glad her character isn't hyper-flanderized, or at least, doesn't appear to be), but Story!Bright shouldn't even be the director of his own god damn office.</p>
<p>Sorry, man. No vote.</p>

